TY  - JOUR
AU  - Garicano, Luis
AU  - Rossi-Hansberg, Esteban
T1  - Organization and Inequality in a Knowledge Economy*
PY  - 2006
Y1  - 2006/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/121.4.1383
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 121
IS  - 4
SP  - 1383
EP  - 1435
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We present an equilibrium theory of the organization of work in an economy where knowledge is an essential input in production and agents are heterogeneous in skill. Agents organize production by matching with others in knowledge hierarchies designed to use and communicate their knowledge efficiently. Relative to autarky, organization leads to larger cross-sectional differences in knowledge and wages: low skill workers learn and earn relatively less. We show that improvements in the technology to acquire knowledge lead to opposite implications on wage inequality and organization than reductions in communication costs.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/121.4.1383
ER  - 



